You know, I got curious here, and I think we could simplify this function as:

    const getAllShownJobs = pushId => (
      Object.values(getJobMap())
        .map(jobEl => jobEl.job_obj)
        .filter(job => job.result_set_id === pushId && job.visible)
    );

It could be made a bit more efficient with a  ``reduce`` but this isn't a costly operation, so I think this works pretty well.  How about we go with this?

For retro-compatibility, we could add a ``from_colander`` method (?)

```python
    @classmethod
    def from_colander(klass, colander_schema, **kwargs):
        # XXX: ...written on a hungry stomache:
        class BodySchema(CorniceSchema):
            body = colander_schema
        return BodySchema(**kwargs)
```

